    <!-- ── INTRO ── -->
    <section class="sw-section">
      <div class="sw-prose">
        <p>
          The second branch of the modern priesthood does not wear lab coats. It wears vestments, business suits, and designer sneakers. It operates from stages, not laboratories. It uses worship music, not equations. But the function is identical to every priesthood that has ever existed: it stands between the people and the Creator, claims authority to interpret truth, and punishes those who dissent — not with peer review, but with excommunication, social exile, and spiritual intimidation.
        </p>
        <p>
          This page examines six faces of that same priesthood, grouped under three categories.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>The Foundation</strong> — the Roman Church that absorbed sun worship into its altars, and the Protestant daughters who walked out of her house still carrying her clothes.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>The Wolves</strong> — the modern false prophets who stand on camera selling words Yahuah never spoke, and the megachurches that have turned worship into a stadium-sized shopping experience.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>The Network</strong> — the New Apostolic Reformation that has built a global hierarchy of self-appointed apostles, and the Political Christianity that has married Yahuah's kingdom to the kingdoms of this world.
        </p>
        <p>
          Each button below opens a full study. These are not six different problems. They are six faces of one priesthood — the priesthood Yahushua came to break, the one that keeps rebuilding itself in every generation, and the one that His people are called in Revelation 18:4 to come out of while there is still time.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

